intro: Tarenna annamensis, commonly known as the Annam tarenna, is a flowering plant native to Southeast Asia. It belongs to the Rubiaceae family, which includes coffee and gardenias. The plant is characterized by its small, fragrant flowers and oval-shaped leaves. It typically grows in tropical rainforests and is often found in the understory of dense vegetation. Due to its limited distribution and habitat specificity, it is considered a rare and endangered species.
